# Global Rules

- This project is TARUMT Marketplace, a second-hand marketplace for TARUMT students, lecturers, and tutors.
- Prioritize clean, reusable, and maintainable code.
- Avoid redundant code and duplicate logic.
- Use meaningful names for files, variables, functions, classes, and components.
- Keep files focused on one responsibility.
- Reuse existing components, hooks, services, DTOs, and utilities before creating new ones.
- Follow the project module scope: marketplace browsing, wishlist, listing, negotiation, bidding, chat, order, review, profile, report, and recommendation engine.
- Do not overcomplicate features unless required for FYP demonstration.
